        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">From Mr. C. Darwin, Down, Beckenham</hi>.</placeName>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>Have you seen an article on you by a great man, Delboeuf, in Revue Scientifique no—17<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> May 24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 79?—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> It has pleased me <hi rend="doubleUnderline">greatly</hi> on your account.— I suppose you c<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. easily see it in London; otherwise I could lend it you.—</p>
<p>C.D</p>
<p>No answer necessary <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">May. 26<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 <hi rend="italic">Mr.</hi>] <hi rend="italic">altered from</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">Mrs.</hi>’ </note>
            </div>
             
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">In his article ‘Le sens des couleurs chez les animaux d’après M. Grant-Allen’ in <hi rend="italic">Revue scientifique de la France et de l’étranger</hi>, 24 May 1879 (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_10930.xml">Delboeuf 1879</ref>), <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1283.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Joseph Delboeuf</ref> had reviewed Allen’s book on the colour sense (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_10344.xml">G. Allen 1879a</ref>).</note>
        </div>  
      
